      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WORKING CLASS GIRL (10) will find this much easier than her last start in Midweek company where she was outclassed. Down to a country maiden here and gets in light after the claim of Nottle. Not an overly strong maiden here and she can put her best foot forward third-up. I HAD A DREAM (1) has missed narrowly in his past couple, going under in a photo finish last time out at this track and trip as favourite. Watson now takes the ride from a favourable alley and there's no reason why he can't go one better. MISS ROMPIN (9) was sound first-up at Mt Barker when 4.1L away and the form out of that race has been good. McNaught rides now and she's expected to have come on from the fresh run. Can make her presence felt. GOD'S WRATH (2) has had a few goes now but his best figures rates highly in this field. DESERT MADAME (6) is better than we saw last start and can improve coming back in trip.",
